# Backend Deployment (Cloud Functions)

When deploying backend changes to Cloud Functions, follow these steps in order.
See docs/DEPLOYMENT.md for full details.

## Pre-deploy

1. Run `./scripts/prepare-functions.sh` from the repo root to copy shared Python
   modules from `gcp/shared/` into each function directory.

## Deploy

2. `cd terraform/environments/prod`
3. `terraform init`
4. `terraform plan` -- review the plan; only the changed functions should update.
5. `terraform apply` -- type 'yes' when prompted.

## Validate

6. `./scripts/validate-deployment.sh mikiri-demo-test northamerica-northeast1`
7. Spot-check updated functions:
   `gcloud functions describe FUNCTION_NAME --project=mikiri-demo-test --region=northamerica-northeast1 --gen2 --format="value(updateTime)"`

## Key details

- Project: `mikiri-demo-test`, Region: `northamerica-northeast1`
- Terraform detects function changes via MD5 hash of source archives.
- All functions are defined in `terraform/modules/core/functions.tf`.
- If terraform apply fails on Eventarc/Workflows service agents, wait 5-10 min and retry.
